HEADWORD: Snary
<hw>Snar"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Snare</er>.]</ety> <def>Resembling, or consisting of, snares;
entangling; insidious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Spiders in the vault their <qex>snary</qex> webs have spread.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snast</ent>⟦br⟧
